INSERT INTO `books_transport` VALUES (1,'Fines','<p>It is necessary to say that one should definitely pay the transportation in Italy. When controlers arrive there is no way out - even if you do not have money! There is no way to negotiate the fine - it can only increase it! The fine is usually 50 euro. After paying it you will pay the usual 1 euro ticket. If you can not pay the fine right then you will get the receipt that needs to be payed to Ufficio Abbonamenti e Informazioni ATAF. If you are late for this pay you will need to pay 200 euro!</p>','transport.jpg'),(2,'Metro and buses in Rome','<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\">You can buy tickets for metro and bus in giornals kiosk (giornalaio) or in Tabacco store (tabacci) or inside metro mashines. Ticket is valid 75 minutes on ground trip or 1 trip on metro</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\"><strong>Types of tickets:</strong></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\"><strong>Biglietto</strong> - 1 euro, valid for 75 minutes ( 1 metro trip). During this time you can make any number of ground trips and 1 underground trip only</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\"><strong>Biglietto giornaliero o BIG</strong> - 4.10 euro can be used during all day for any number of trips in metro, bus, tram and suburban trains within the city. One should punch it&nbsp;at the first entrance and it will be valid 24 hours</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\"><strong>Biglietto turistico integrato BIT</strong> (11 EURO)- valid 3 days</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\"><strong>Carta settimanale CIS</strong> (16 EURO) - it is a personal document, valid 1 week. You will write your name, year and place of birth&nbsp;on it. When it is controlled you should present your passport or driving licence.</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Roman metro</strong> - is the underground system of transportation in Rome. It was open in 1955. It consists of A (red)&nbsp;and B (blue)&nbsp;lines. Right now there are construction works to create C line (green). Metro working hours 5.30 - 23.30, saturday till 00.30</div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Ð¡ost of metro ticket:</strong> 1 Ðµuro<br /><strong>Cost of bus tickets:</strong> 1.20 Ðµuro, ticket is purshased inside the bus</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">Travelling time from Termini to Anagnina is 20 minutes.</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">From Anagnina to Ciampino travelling time is 25 minutes<br /><br /><strong>Metro&nbsp;works:</strong> 5.30-23.30, on saturday&nbsp;till 00.30 <br /><strong></strong></div>','metro.jpg'),(3,'Taxi in Rome','<p>Taxi in Rome is quite expensive. Short trips are not convenient - the first 7 kilometres will cost you not less than 4 euro and then 0, 7 euro per kilometre. On Sundays and holidays the rate is 0,6 euro per kilometre higher. Also, at night, 22.00 - 07.00 the rate wil be 2 euro higher.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Taxi</strong> from Termini to Ciampino - 35-40 Ðµuro</p>','taxi.jpg'),(4,'How to reach the centre of Rome from airport Fiumicino','<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\">Roman international airport, oficcially called Leonardo da Vinci Fiumicino consists of 3 terminals -A, B, C. International flights are received to B and C terminals. How to reach Rome from Fiumicino?</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>1) On express train</strong></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">There is the express train to Termini station from Fiumicino. It goes from 6.37 till 22.52. The trip lasts 31 minutes. You will find it according to the indications Stazione FS within terminal. One trip costs 14 euro. Children below 12 years old are free. Tickets are sold at cashier desk or in mashines. Once you arrive to Termini you can walk to Metro signed if you need to take the metro.</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>2) On the bus</strong></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">Also, you can take a bus from Fiumicino.</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">Terravision Shuttle goes every 2 hours, 8.30 - 20.30 and one trip costs 7 euro.</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">Schiaffini Travel Shuttle goes twice a day from 8.30 till 20.30 , one trip costs 8 euro.</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">Cotral buses of this company run without scedule, trip will cost 5 euro.</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>3) Taxi</strong></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">Taxi from the airport will cost 45 - 50 euro</div>','fiumicino.jpg'),(5,'How to reach the centre of Rome from Ciampino airport ','<p><strong>1) By train</strong></p>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">From Termini station to Ciampino train goes every 15 - 20 minutes from 5.34 till 22.42. Trip lasts 15 minutes. You can see the scedule on Trenitalia site.</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>2) By bus&nbsp;</strong></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">From Ciampino railway station till airport Fiumicino Schiaffini Autoline runs buses.</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><br /><strong>3) By metro and then by bus</strong></div>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">From Anagnina railway station by A metro line there are buses from platform 1</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>','ciampino.jpg');
